<pre><code>public static URL getLimelightURLString(String tableName, String request) {
    String urlString = "http://" + sanitizeName(tableName) + ".local:5807/" + request;
    URL url;
    try {
        url = new URL(urlString);
        return url;
    } catch (MalformedURLException e) {
        System.err.println("bad LL URL");
    }
    return null;
}
</code></pre>
<p>that they have in a library provide data on multiple objects it sees? I assume the NT call does not, since I do not see such data in NT.</p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":5,"updated_at":"2023-09-24T23:05:57.500Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":179,"readers_count":178,"score":40.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":441389,"topic_slug":"limelight-with-google-coral-multiple-gamepiece-targets","display_username":"Alex Tsekhansky","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":44471,"username":"jonahb55","name":"Jonah Bonner","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/jonahb55/{size}/194474_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":50762,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/limelight-with-google-coral-multiple-gamepiece-targets/441389/3","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3234753,"name":"Jonah Bonner","username":"jonahb55","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/jonahb55/{size}/194474_2.png","created_at":"2023-09-24T23:40:51.883Z","cooked":"<p>The JSON data is published to NT under the “json” topic — you can access it that way using the “getLatestResult” method in the library. The specification says that it supports multiple targets, and that is reflected in the library (“Results” includes an <em>array</em> of “LimelightTarget_Detector”).</p>","post_num